430→\n   431→**stage**\n   432→A named step in a flow preset. Stage is the normalized term replacing today’s overloaded phase language.\n   433→\n   434→**stage cursor**\n   435→The current durable position in a run:\n   436→\n   437→* current stage\n   438→* current cycle\n   439→* current iteration/attempt metadata\n   440→\n   441→**work cycle**\n   442→The normal unit of iterative delivery work. This replaces today’s overloaded “loop” internally. CLI may still expose “cycle” rather than “loop.”\n   443→\n   444→**completion round**\n   445→A distinct round for deciding complete vs continue. It is not the same as a work cycle.\n   446→\n   447→**role**\n   448→A logical actor in a stage, such as planner, implementer, reviewer, QA, completer, or final reviewer.\n   449→\n   450→**backend family**\n   451→A backend provider family such as Claude, Codex, or OpenRouter.\n   452→\n   453→**backend spec**\n   454→A typed backend selection plus optional model spec.\n   455→\n   456→**model spec**\n   457→The backend-native model identifier.\n   458→\n   459→**stage contract**\n   460→The machine contract for a stage’s output:\n   461→\n   462→* schema\n   463→* required fields\n   464→* semantic validation rules\n   465→\n   466→**stage payload**\n   467→The canonical structured output for a stage after validation.\n   468→\n   469→**history artifact**\n   470→A durable, human-readable markdown rendering derived from a validated stage payload and stored as project history.\n   471→\n   472→**runtime log**\n   473→Ephemeral operational or debug output for immediate troubleshooting. Runtime logs are not part of durable project history.\n   474→\n   475→**journal**\n   476→An append-only event stream of run and project transitions.\n   477→\n   478→**validation profile**\n   479→A reusable set of validation behaviors, such as:\n   480→\n   481→* `standard`\n   482→* `quick_dev`\n   483→* `docs_change`\n   484→* `ci_improvement`\n   485→\n   486→**requirements draft**\n   487→The modernized external CLI term for what the old repo often called PRD generation.\n   488→\n   489→**session record**\n   490→A durable record for backend session continuity, if used.\n   491→\n   492→**amendment request**\n   493→A requested change to be reintroduced into work, often after final review or external direction.\n   494→\n   495→**rollback point**\n   496→A durable reference to a logical and optionally VCS-backed rewind target.\n   497→\n   498→**task**\n   499→A daemon-owned unit of automated work, usually associated with an issue or PR.\n   500→\n   501→**routing command**\n   502→An explicit issue/PR command such as `/rb run` or `/rb flow docs_change`.\n   503→\n   504→**routing label**\n   505→A label used by the daemon to infer dispatch behavior, such as `rb:flow:ci_improvement`.\n   506→\n   507→# Bounded Contexts\n   508→\n   509→Before defining contexts, the repo-specific starting hypotheses should be resolved like this:\n   510→\n   511→* **Workflow Orchestration** → becomes **Workflow Composition**\n   512→* **Backend Execution** → becomes **Agent Execution**\n   513→* **Project Lifecycle** → becomes part of **Project & Run Record**\n   514→* **Workspace Management** → becomes **Workspace Governance**\n   515→* **Validation/Conformance** → split into:\n   516→\n   517→  * **Validation Profiles** inside Workflow Composition\n   518→  * **Conformance Specification** as its own context\n   519→* **PRD Pipeline** → becomes **Requirements Drafting**\n   520→* **Git Integration** → not a bounded context; it is an adapter cluster\n   521→* **Prompt/Template Management** → not a bounded context; it is an adapter cluster\n   522→* **CLI / User Command Surface** → not a bounded context; it is a driving adapter\n   523→* **Configuration / Policy Resolution** → becomes part of **Workspace Governance**\n   524→\n   525→## Workspace Governance\n   526→\n   527→* **Name**\n   528→  Workspace Governance\n   529→\n   530→* **Purpose**\n   531→  Own workspace initialization, workspace versioning, active project selection, effective config resolution, and flow/template discovery.\n   532→\n   533→* **Why this boundary exists**\n   534→  These rules are shared across run, requirements, and daemon paths, but they are not delivery policy.\n   535→\n   536→* **Responsibilities**\n   537→\n   538→  * initialize `.ralph-burning/`\n   539→  * persist workspace config\n   540→  * resolve active project\n   541→  * resolve effective config from defaults/workspace/project/runtime layers\n   542→  * expose flow preset catalog metadata\n   543→  * resolve prompt/template sources\n   544→  * validate workspace version\n   545→\n   546→* **What it owns**\n   547→\n   548→  * workspace metadata\n   549→  * active project semantics\n   550→  * config precedence\n   551→  * workspace version contract\n   552→  * flow preset discovery surface\n   553→\n   554→* **What it explicitly does not own**\n   555→\n   556→  * run transitions\n   557→  * project history\n   558→  * backend invocation\n   559→  * requirements stage logic\n   560→  * GitHub task lifecycle\n   561→\n   562→* **Core concepts**\n   563→\n   564→  * Workspace\n   565→  * ActiveProjectRef\n   566→  * EffectiveConfig\n   567→  * FlowCatalogView\n   568→  * TemplateSource\n   569→  * WorkspaceVersion\n   570→\n   571→* **Entities**\n   572→\n   573→  * Workspace\n   574→\n   575→* **Value objects**\n   576→\n   577→  * WorkspaceRoot\n   578→  * ProjectSelector\n   579→  * ConfigScope\n   580→  * EffectiveWorkflowPolicy\n   581→  * EffectiveValidationPolicy\n   582→  * EffectiveBackendPolicy\n   583→\n   584→* **Aggregates**\n   585→\n   586→  * None worth forcing. This is largely application/configuration logic.\n   587→\n   588→* **Domain/application services**\n   589→\n   590→  * InitializeWorkspace\n   591→  * ValidateWorkspace\n   592→  * ResolveActiveProject\n   593→  * ResolveEffectiveConfig\n   594→  * ListFlows\n   595→  * ShowFlow\n   596→\n   597→* **Invariants/business rules**\n   598→\n   599→  * runtime overrides beat project config\n   600→  * project config beats workspace config\n   601→  * workspace config beats code defaults\n   602→  * unsupported workspace versions fail clearly\n   603→  * active project must exist or resolution fails\n   604→  * only built-in flow presets are selectable in v1\n   605→\n   606→* **Commands**\n   607→\n   608→  * InitializeWorkspace\n   609→  * SetActiveProject\n   610→  * UpdateConfig\n   611→  * ValidateWorkspace\n   612→\n   613→* **Events**\n   614→\n   615→  * WorkspaceInitialized\n   616→  * ActiveProjectChanged\n   617→  * ConfigUpdated\n   618→\n   619→* **Queries/read models**\n   620→\n   621→  * workspace summary\n   622→  * effective config\n   623→  * active project summary\n   624→  * flow list\n   625→  * flow details\n   626→\n   627→* **Inbound dependencies**\n   628→\n   629→  * CLI\n   630→  * Workflow Composition\n   631→  * Requirements Drafting\n   632→  * Automation Runtime\n   633→  * Project & Run Record\n   634→\n   635→* **Outbound dependencies**\n   636→\n   637→  * WorkspaceStorePort\n   638→  * ConfigStorePort\n   639→  * TemplateCatalogPort\n   640→  * LockPort\n   641→\n   642→* **Data ownership**\n   643→\n   644→  * `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml`\n   645→  * active-project marker\n   646→  * template source metadata if persisted\n   647→\n   648→* **Trust/sensitivity concerns**\n   649→\n   650→  * local config and template paths are untrusted input\n   651→  * path traversal and malformed config must fail safely\n   652→\n   653→* **Likely code/package/module boundary**\n   654→\n   655→  * `contexts/workspace_governance/*`\n   656→\n   657→## Project & Run Record\n   658→\n   659→* **Name**\n   660→  Project & Run Record\n   661→\n   662→* **Purpose**\n   663→  Own canonical project metadata, run state, journal, durable history, runtime log classification, sessions, amendments, rollback points, and operator queries.\n   664→\n   665→* **Why this boundary exists**\n   666→  The current repo spreads durable behavior across `src/project/*` and reconstructs too much from artifacts. The rewrite needs a clean source of truth.\n   667→\n   668→* **Responsibilities**\n   669→\n   670→  * create/list/show/delete/select projects\n   671→  * persist canonical project state\n   672→  * persist canonical run state\n   673→  * append journal entries\n   674→  * store stage payload records\n   675→  * store rendered history artifacts\n   676→  * classify/store runtime logs separately\n   677→  * manage session records\n   678→  * manage amendment queue\n   679→  * manage rollback points\n   680→  * serve status/history/tail/rollback queries\n   681→\n   682→* **What it owns**\n   683→\n   684→  * project identity\n   685→  * selected flow preset\n   686→  * prompt reference/hash\n   687→  * active run\n   688→  * stage cursor\n   689→  * work cycle history\n   690→  * completion round history\n   691→  * durable payload index\n   692→  * durable artifact index\n   693→  * runtime log metadata\n   694→  * session records\n   695→  * amendment queue\n   696→  * rollback points\n   697→\n   698→* **What it explicitly does not own**\n   699→\n   700→  * stage transition policy\n   701→  * backend CLI mechanics\n   702→  * prompt rendering\n   703→  * GitHub routing decisions\n   704→  * validation profile selection logic\n   705→\n   706→* **Core concepts**\n   707→\n   708→  * ProjectRecord\n   709→  * RunRecord\n   710→  * StageCursor\n   711→  * WorkCycle\n   712→  * CompletionRound\n   713→  * PayloadRecord\n   714→  * ArtifactRecord\n   715→  * RuntimeLogRecord\n   716→  * SessionRecord\n   717→  * AmendmentQueue\n   718→  * RollbackPoint\n   719→\n   720→* **Entities**\n   721→\n   722→  * ProjectRecord\n   723→  * RunRecord\n   724→  * WorkCycleRecord\n   725→  * CompletionRoundRecord\n   726→  * PayloadRecord\n   727→  * ArtifactRecord\n   728→  * RuntimeLogRecord\n   729→  * SessionRecord\n   730→  * AmendmentRequest\n   731→\n   732→* **Value objects**\n   733→\n   734→  * ProjectId\n   735→  * RunId\n   736→  * FlowId\n   737→  * StageId\n   738→  * CycleNumber\n   739→  * CompletionRoundNumber\n   740→  * PayloadId\n   741→  * ArtifactId\n   742→  * LogId\n   743→  * PromptHash\n   744→  * CheckpointRef\n   745→\n   746→* **Aggregates**\n   747→\n   748→  * `ProjectRecord` is the main aggregate\n   749→  * `RunRecord` can be a nested aggregate\n   750→\n   751→* **Domain/application services**\n   752→\n   753→  * CreateProject\n   754→  * DeleteProject\n   755→  * StartRun\n   756→  * LoadProject\n   757→  * SaveProject\n   758→  * RecordStageResult\n   759→  * AppendJournalEvent\n   760→  * EnqueueAmendment\n   761→  * ClaimAmendments\n   762→  * RecordRuntimeLog\n   763→  * QueryStatus\n   764→  * QueryHistory\n   765→  * QueryTail\n   766→  * RollbackProject\n   767→\n   768→* **Invariants/business rules**\n   769→\n   770→  * one active run per project\n   771→  * one immutable flow preset per project\n   772→  * stage cursor must reference a legal stage in that flow\n   773→  * work cycle numbering is monotonic\n   774→  * completion round numbering is monotonic and separate\n   775→  * history artifacts are durable project history\n   776→  * runtime logs are not durable history\n   777→  * snapshot writes are atomic\n   778→  * journal append precedes exposed read-model updates\n   779→  * rollback points are durable and queryable\n   780→\n   781→* **Commands**\n   782→\n   783→  * CreateProject\n   784→  * DeleteProject\n   785→  * StartRun\n   786→  * RecordStageResult\n   787→  * EnqueueAmendment\n   788→  * RecordRuntimeLog\n   789→  * RollbackProject\n   790→  * ResetSessions\n   791→\n   792→* **Events**\n   793→\n   794→  * ProjectCreated\n   795→  * RunStarted\n   796→  * StageCompleted\n   797→  * StageRejected\n   798→  * CycleCompleted\n   799→  * CompletionRoundRecorded"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TEaD8r9ay6pGSRWy6ah8ZA","session_id":"62aed473