{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018rd9hAizfQ9ujspstjUwB1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Loop 6 Implementation Notes: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\n     2→\n     3→## Decisions\n     4→\n     5→### Engine Architecture\n     6→- The orchestration engine lives in `workflow_composition::engine` as a set of free functions rather than a struct, keeping it stateless and easy to test. The engine receives all dependencies as trait-object references.\n     7→- `execute_standard_run` accepts 9 parameters (with `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]`). This was a deliberate trade-off: a config struct would add indirection without reducing complexity, and the engine is called from exactly one CLI entry point.\n     8→\n     9→### Preflight Check Strategy\n    10→- Preflight validates capability + availability for **all** stages before any mutation. This means a single missing backend capability fails the entire run before touching any durable state.\n    11→- The `AgentExecutionService` exposes its inner adapter via `adapter()` so the engine can call `check_capability` / `check_availability` directly, avoiding an unnecessary wrapper layer.\n    12→\n    13→### Atomic Stage Commit\n    14→- Each stage commit writes: payload -> artifact -> journal event -> snapshot update.\n    15→- If artifact write fails, the payload file is cleaned up (rollback). If journal append fails after payload/artifact, a `StageCommitFailed` error is returned.\n    16→- Runtime logs are best-effort (`let _ = ...`) and never affect durable state.\n    17→\n    18→### Stage Plan Derivation\n    19→- `standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled)` filters the flow definition's stage list, removing `PromptReview` when disabled.\n    20→- `role_for_stage` delegates to `BackendRole::for_stage` for deterministic stage-to-role mapping.\n    21→\n    22→### Run ID Generation\n    23→- Format: `run-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS` using `Utc::now()`. Simple and human-readable. No UUID dependency needed for this slice.\n    24→\n    25→### Only Standard Flow\n    26→- Non-standard flows return `UnsupportedFlow` error immediately in the CLI handler, before any engine code runs.\n    27→\n    28→## Deviations\n    29→\n    30→### None\n    31→All 17 acceptance criteria are addressed. No deviations from the spec.\n    32→\n    33→## Files Modified\n    34→\n    35→| File | Change |\n    36→|------|--------|\n    37→| `src/shared/error.rs` | +4 error variants: `RunStartFailed`, `UnsupportedFlow`, `PreflightFailed`, `StageCommitFailed` |\n    38→| `src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` | +`FailedStageSummary` struct, +`Display` impl for `RunStatus` |\n    39→| `src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` | +5 lifecycle event builders: `run_started_event`, `stage_entered_event`, `stage_completed_event`, `run_completed_event`, `run_failed_event` |\n    40→| `src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` | +3 port traits: `RunSnapshotWritePort`, `PayloadArtifactWritePort`, `RuntimeLogWritePort` |\n    41→| `src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` | Updated exports for new port traits |\n    42→| `src/adapters/fs.rs` | +3 adapter structs: `FsRunSnapshotWriteStore`, `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore`, `FsRuntimeLogWriteStore` |\n    43→| `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` | +`adapter()` method on `AgentExecutionService` |\n    44→| `src/cli/run.rs` | Rewrote `handle_start()` from stub to full orchestration |\n    45→\n    46→## Files Created\n    47→\n    48→| File | Purpose |\n    49→|------|---------|\n    50→| `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` | Core orchestration engine with stage plan derivation, preflight checks, and stage execution loop |\n    51→| `tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` | 10 unit tests for engine functions |\n    52→| `tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature` | 17 Gherkin scenarios for run start conformance |\n    53→\n    54→## Testing\n    55→\n    56→### Unit Tests (185 total, all pass)\n    57→- `workflow_engine_test`: 10 tests covering stage plan derivation, role mapping, preflight checks, happy path execution, and failure handling\n    58→- `project_run_record_test`: 4 new tests for `FailedStageSummary` serialization, `RunStatus::Display`, and terminal snapshot states\n    59→- All pre-existing tests continue to pass\n    60→\n    61→### CLI Integration Tests (63 total, all pass)\n    62→- 10 new `run start` tests:\n    63→  - `run_start_completes_standard_flow_end_to_end` - happy path\n    64→  - `run_start_produces_completed_snapshot` - verifies run.json state\n    65→  - `run_start_persists_journal_events` - verifies all lifecycle events\n    66→  - `run_start_persists_payload_and_artifact_records` - verifies 8 payload + 8 artifact files\n    67→  - `run_start_status_shows_completed_after_run` - post-run query validation\n    68→  - `run_start_rejects_non_standard_flow` - UnsupportedFlow error\n    69→  - `run_start_rejects_already_completed_project` - precondition check\n    70→  - `run_start_rejects_already_running_project` - precondition check\n    71→  - `run_start_without_active_project_fails` - no active project error\n    72→\n    73→### Gherkin Conformance\n    74→- 17 scenarios in `run_start_standard.feature` covering all acceptance criteria\n    75→\n    76→### Build Verification\n    77→- `cargo check --all-targets`: pass\n    78→- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`: pass\n    79→- `cargo test`: 248 tests pass (185 unit + 63 CLI integration)\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TEaD8r9ay6pGSRWy6ah8ZA","session_id":"62aed473-a912-4db2-a48b-52d5c598eaf3","uuid":"c5108e5b-132e-4a82-b02c-f46019250dbe"}
