{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RdKWbKBgx7udHSv6tamdbf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Daemon Lifecycle Commands\n     2→  The daemon foreground loop processes pending tasks, exposes status, and\n     3→  supports abort and retry transitions for terminal recovery flows.\n     4→\n     5→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-001\n     6→  Scenario: Daemon start processes one pending task in a single iteration\n     7→    Given a git-backed workspace with a pending daemon task\n     8→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon start --single-iteration\"\n     9→    Then the daemon claims the task\n    10→    And the daemon rebases the task worktree onto the default branch\n    11→    And the task finishes in a terminal status\n    12→    And the task lease is released\n    13→\n    14→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-002\n    15→  Scenario: Daemon status lists non-terminal tasks first\n    16→    Given daemon tasks exist in statuses \"pending\", \"active\", and \"completed\"\n    17→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon status\"\n    18→    Then the non-terminal tasks appear before the completed task\n    19→    And each row includes lease and heartbeat data when present\n    20→\n    21→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-003\n    22→  Scenario: Abort transitions a claimed task to aborted and cleans up its lease\n    23→    Given a claimed daemon task with a persisted lease\n    24→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    25→    Then the task transitions to \"aborted\"\n    26→    And the worktree lease is released\n    27→    And the task worktree is removed\n    28→\n    29→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-004\n    30→  Scenario: Retry returns a failed task to pending\n    31→    Given a daemon task in status \"failed\"\n    32→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon retry <task-id>\"\n    33→    Then the task transitions to \"pending\"\n    34→    And the task attempt count is incremented\n    35→\n    36→  # DAEMON-LIFECYCLE-005\n    37→  Scenario: Abort rejects terminal tasks\n    38→    Given a daemon task in status \"completed\"\n    39→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>\"\n    40→    Then the command fails with \"TaskStateTransitionInvalid\"\n    41→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TEaD8r9ay6pGSRWy6ah8ZA","session_id":"62aed473-a912-4db2-a48b-52d5c598eaf3","uuid":"c2b5e9c3-86c2-42f5-b72e-4afaad1f945f"}
