{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TEaD8r9ay6pGSRWy6ah8ZA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me create a detailed summary report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: ralph-burning-rewrite Project\n\nBased on thorough exploration of the codebase, specification documents, feature files, and implementation notes, here's what has been built:\n\n### **Project Overview**\n\nThe `ralph-burning-rewrite` is a Rust-based greenfield rewrite of an AI-driven orchestration system. It's a modular monolith implementing sophisticated workflow automation for software delivery, requirements drafting, and daemon-driven task execution. The rewrite departs from the legacy codebase's design, introducing structured JSON payloads, bounded contexts, and a modern CLI vocabulary.\n\n**Current Status**: Actively under development with 14 completed implementation loops (as of March 13, 2026).\n\n---\n\n### **Implemented Slices (Mapping to rb.md Roadmap)**\n\n#### **Slice 1: Rewrite Charter & CLI Vocabulary** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Product renamed to `ralph-burning` throughout\n- Workspace root standardized as `.ralph-burning/`\n- CLI vocabulary: `init`, `flow`, `config`, `project`, `run`, `requirements`, `daemon`, `conformance`\n- 4 built-in flow presets: `standard`, `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, `ci_improvement`\n- 201 Gherkin scenarios defined across 18 feature files\n- Conformance scenario discovery and validation framework in place\n\n#### **Slice 2: Workflow Kernel Primitives & Stage Contract Framework** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `FlowPreset` enum with 4 variants and metadata\n- `StageId` enum with 16 stages covering all 4 presets\n- `StageContract` with schema → domain validation → render pipeline\n- `BackendRole` deterministic mapping (planner, implementer, QA validator, reviewer, completion judge)\n- `FailureClass` enum: TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n- Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic and consistent\n- Payload validation contracts for all stage types\n\n#### **Slice 3: Workspace Governance & Flow Discovery** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml` initialization with version support\n- Effective config resolution (runtime overrides > project config > workspace config > code defaults)\n- Active project selection and persistence\n- `flow list` and `flow show` commands\n- Workspace validation and versioning (currently v1)\n- Template source resolution framework\n\n#### **Slice 4: Canonical Project & Run Store** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `ProjectRecord` aggregate with immutable flow preset\n- `RunRecord` with run ID, status, and stage cursor\n- Durable journal with monotonically-increasing sequence numbers\n- Payload store with validated stage outputs\n- Artifact store with rendered Markdown history\n- Runtime log store (separate from durable history)\n- `run status`, `run history`, `run tail` query commands\n- Session management for backend continuity\n- Amendment queue for late-stage changes\n- Rollback point persistence\n\n#### **Slice 5: Agent Execution with Structured Output Guarantee** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `AgentExecutionService` with pluggable backends\n- `BackendSpec` and `ModelSpec` for 4 backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n- `InvocationContract` enum supporting both workflow stages and requirements\n- Capability checking (structured output support, session reuse, cancellation)\n- Timeout/cancellation with session cleanup\n- Raw output persistence for debugging\n- Test injection seams for all failure modes\n\n#### **Slice 6: First Vertical Slice - Standard Happy Path** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `run start` command end-to-end orchestration\n- 8-stage standard flow execution: prompt_review → planning → implementation → QA → review → completion_panel → acceptance_QA → final_review\n- Prompt review optionally skippable (7 stages when disabled)\n- Preflight validation of all stage targets before any mutation\n- Atomic stage commits: payload → artifact → journal → snapshot\n- Journal event lifecycle: run_started → stage_entered → stage_completed → run_completed/run_failed\n- Terminal run states with error summaries\n- Post-run queries work correctly (status, history, tail)\n\n#### **Slice 7: Resilience Semantics** ✅ COMPLETE\n- QA remediation loop (request_changes causes re-execution)\n- Review remediation loop (request_changes causes re-planning)\n- Prompt review stage with rejection/approval paths\n- Pre-commit invalidation (failed validation causes re-implementation)\n- `run resume` command for recovering mid-run states\n- Failure-class retry policy (transient vs terminal)\n- Session reuse/reset rules per backend capability\n- Cycle counting and attempt tracking\n\n#### **Slice 8: Completion & Final Review** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Completion rounds distinct from work cycles\n- Completion panel stage with consensus logic\n- Acceptance QA with pass/fail outcomes\n- Final review stage (preset-specific enablement)\n- Amendment queue: typed `QueuedAmendment` with source tracking\n- Late-stage vs remediation-stage separation\n- Amendment persistence before state mutation (durable lifecycle)\n- Amendment injection into planning context\n- Completion guard prevents `run_completed` while amendments pending\n- Amendment drain after successful planning commit\n\n#### **Slice 9: Preset Library Expansion** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `quick_dev` preset: PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview (4 stages)\n- `docs_change` preset: DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation (3 stages, completion disabled)\n- `ci_improvement` preset: CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation (3 stages, completion disabled)\n- Preset-specific stage contracts and validators\n- Preset-specific final-review policy\n- All 4 presets share the same workflow engine\n- Deterministic role mapping per stage across all presets\n\n#### **Slice 10: Requirements Drafting & Project Seed Handoff** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `requirements draft` with clarifying question generation\n- `requirements quick` skipping questions\n- `requirements show` displaying run state\n- `requirements answer` with TOML parsing and validation\n- Draft → Review → Seed pipeline with validated payloads\n- Question set contract: duplicate ID validation\n- Requirements review contract: outcome + findings validation\n- Project seed generation (project.json + prompt.md)\n- Seed pair rollback on failure\n- Persistent seed files for project creation\n- Resume from answer boundary\n\n#### **Slice 11: Automation Runtime** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Daemon lifecycle: `daemon start --single-iteration`\n- Task model with statuses: pending, active, completed, aborted, failed\n- Task routing: label-based and explicit command-based\n- Worktree leasing with persistent leases\n- Worktree rebase onto default branch\n- `daemon status` with task listing\n- `daemon abort` with task transition and cleanup\n- `daemon retry` returning failed tasks to pending\n- `daemon reconcile` for state recovery\n- Attempt counting for failed task retries\n- Journal events for task lifecycle\n\n#### **Slice 12: Cutover & Documentation** 🟡 IN PROGRESS (Loop 14 active)\n- Legacy orchestrator code paths still present but new runtime active\n- Conformance suite mandatory in test matrix\n- Context packs framework in place\n- CLI cutover to new command routing 100% complete\n- Documentation refresh in progress (loops 11-14)\n\n---\n\n### **Core Module Structure**\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── shared/\n│   ├── domain.rs       — Shared enums (FlowPreset, StageId, BackendFamily, etc.)\n│   ├── error.rs        — Unified error types (AppError enum)\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── contexts/           — 7 bounded contexts\n│   ├── workspace_governance/    — Init, config, flow discovery\n│   ├── project_run_record/      — Project/run CRUD, journal, artifacts\n│   ├── workflow_composition/    — Engine, stage execution, retry policy\n│   ├── agent_execution/         — Backend invocation, capabilities, sessions\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/   — Requirements pipeline, contracts, service\n│   ├── automation_runtime/      — Daemon, routing, leases, tasks\n│   └── conformance_spec/        — Scenario discovery, runner, validation\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── fs.rs           — All filesystem persistence (project, journal, runs, amendments, etc.)\n│   ├── stub_backend.rs — Test-only deterministic backend\n│   └── worktree.rs     — Git worktree operations\n├── cli/                — 8 command modules\n│   ├── init.rs         — Workspace initialization\n│   ├── flow.rs         — Flow list/show\n│   ├── config.rs       — Config get/set/show\n│   ├── project.rs      — Project CRUD\n│   ├── run.rs          — Run start/resume/status/history/tail/rollback\n│   ├── requirements.rs — Requirements draft/quick/show/answer\n│   ├── daemon.rs       — Daemon start/status/abort/retry/reconcile\n│   └── conformance.rs  — Conformance list/run\n├── lib.rs              — Library exports\n└── main.rs             — CLI entry point\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Coverage**\n\n**Total Gherkin Scenarios**: 201 across 18 feature files\n\n| Feature File | Scenarios | Coverage |\n|---|---|---|\n| run_start_standard.feature | 20 | Happy path, error cases, preflight, atomic commits |\n| run_completion_rounds.feature | 16 | Completion semantics, amendments, late stages |\n| run_queries.feature | 28 | Status, history, tail queries, filtering |\n| requirements_drafting.feature | 33 | Draft/quick modes, answers, review, seed rollback |\n| project_records.feature | 23 | Project CRUD, flow immutability, state transitions |\n| run_resume_retry.feature | 9 | Resume from interrupted states, retry logic |\n| run_resume_non_standard.feature | 6 | Quick_dev/docs/CI preset resume |\n| daemon_lifecycle.feature | 5 | Task processing, abort, retry, status |\n| daemon_routing.feature | 7 | Label/command routing, task dispatch |\n| run_rollback.feature | 8 | Rollback points, VCS reset, state recovery |\n| run_start_quick_dev.feature | 10 | Quick_dev preset 4-stage execution |\n| run_start_docs_change.feature | 5 | Docs preset 3-stage execution |\n| run_start_ci_improvement.feature | 5 | CI preset 3-stage execution |\n| workspace_init.feature | 3 | Workspace initialization, versioning |\n| workspace_config.feature | 8 | Config precedence, validation |\n| flow_discovery.feature | 2 | Flow list/show commands |\n| stage_contracts.feature | 9 | Contract validation pipeline |\n| active_project.feature | 4 | Active project selection, persistence |\n\n**Unit Tests**: 40+ test files covering:\n- Domain models\n- Contract validation pipelines\n- Renderers (determinism testing)\n- Workflow engine state machines\n- Adapter contracts\n- Journal serialization\n- Amendment queue operations\n- Retry policies\n- Conformance discovery\n\n**CLI Integration Tests**: 63+ end-to-end tests exercising all command paths\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Decisions**\n\n1. **Structured Payloads as Protocol**: JSON contracts replace markdown as machine protocol; markdown remains rendered output only\n2. **Flow Immutability**: Each project has one immutable flow preset for entire lifetime\n3. **Bounded Context Separation**: 7 clear domain contexts with explicit port/adapter boundaries\n4. **Stateless Engine**: Workflow orchestration via free functions, not class hierarchy\n5. **Durable Guarantees**: Journal-first approach with atomic commits\n6. **Late-Stage Semantics**: Completion panel/acceptance QA/final review use separate completion-round tracking\n7. **Amendment Queuing**: Amendments persisted to disk before state mutation\n8. **Preset-Specific Policy**: Final review, validation profiles configurable per flow\n9. **Deterministic Stage Mapping**: `BackendRole::for_stage()` is consistent across all invocations\n10. **Test Injection Seams**: Environment variables enable testing all failure modes without mocking\n\n---\n\n### **Known Gaps & Outstanding Work**\n\n1. **Legacy Code Paths**: Old orchestrator code still exists in multibackend-orchestration; cleanout deferred to Slice 12\n2. **GitHub Integration**: Daemon routing framework exists but GitHub API adapter not yet wired\n3. **Interactive Requirements**: Requirements answer-via-issue flow not yet implemented\n4. **Validation Profile Selection**: Defaults hardcoded; custom validation targets not yet configurable\n5. **Backend Timeout Tuning**: Hardcoded defaults; configuration not yet exposed\n6. **Worktree Management**: Basic operations implemented; cleanup policies incomplete\n7. **Documentation**: Architecture docs in progress (loop 14 active)\n8. **Performance**: No benchmarks; optimization deferred post-MVP\n\n---\n\n### **CLI Command Surface** (Fully Implemented)\n\n```\nralph-burning\n├── init [--workspace-dir PATH]\n├── flow\n│   ├── list\n│   └── show <preset>\n├── config\n│   ├── get [KEY]\n│   ├── set KEY VALUE\n│   └── show\n├── project\n│   ├── create [--flow PRESET]\n│   ├── list\n│   ├── show [ID]\n│   ├── select [ID]\n│   └── delete ID\n├── run\n│   ├── start\n│   ├── resume\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── history [--json]\n│   ├── tail [--logs]\n│   └── rollback --to ID [--hard]\n├── requirements\n│   ├── draft --idea TEXT\n│   ├── quick --idea TEXT\n│   ├── show <run-id>\n│   └── answer <run-id>\n├── daemon\n│   ├── start [--single-iteration]\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── abort TASK_ID\n│   ├── retry TASK_ID\n│   └── reconcile\n└── conformance\n    ├── list\n    └── run [--features PATTERN]\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Data Model** (Core Entities)\n\n- **ProjectRecord**: Immutable project with flow preset, prompt, ID\n- **RunRecord**: Run instance with cursor, status, session tracking\n- **StageCursor**: Current position (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- **PayloadRecord**: Validated stage output in canonical JSON\n- **ArtifactRecord**: Rendered Markdown history artifact\n- **JournalEvent**: Append-only audit log with sequence numbers\n- **AmendmentQueue**: Late-stage change requests with source tracking\n- **DaemonTask**: Unit of automated work with routing/status\n- **WorktreeLease**: Claimed worktree with heartbeat\n- **SessionRecord**: Backend session for reuse/reset tracking\n\n---\n\n### **Error Handling Strategy**\n\n- **Unified `AppError` enum**: ~40 variants covering all failure modes\n- **Failure classes**: TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n- **Precondition checks**: Workspace version, active project, run state transitions validated before mutation\n- **Atomicity**: Stage commits roll back payload on artifact failure\n- **Resumability**: All durable boundaries are resumable after failure\n\n---\n\n### **Testing Strategy**\n\n1. **Conformance Scenarios (Gherkin)**: 201 scenarios defining public behavior\n2. **Unit Tests**: Domain model invariants, contract validation, renderers\n3. **Adapter Tests**: Filesystem persistence, mock backends, worktree operations\n4. **CLI Integration Tests**: End-to-end command execution with fixtures\n5. **Determinism Tests**: Stage contracts produce identical Markdown twice\n6. **Failure Mode Tests**: All error paths exercised via environment variable injection\n\n---\n\n### **Performance Characteristics**\n\n- **Stage execution**: Sequential per run (no parallelization within single stage)\n- **Payload validation**: O(n) schema + O(1-n) domain per stage\n- **Journal operations**: Append-only (O(1) append, O(n) scan on resume)\n- **Conformance discovery**: O(m·s) where m=feature files, s=scenarios per file\n- **No database**: All persistence via filesystem (TOML, JSON, Markdown)\n\n---\n\n### **Notable Design Patterns**\n\n- **Port/Adapter**: Clear trait boundaries for filesystem, backends, worktrees\n- **Strategy Pattern**: `InvocationContract` enum routing to stage/requirements handlers\n- **Atomic Commits**: Payload → artifact → journal → snapshot ordering prevents partial state\n- **Best-Effort Logs**: Runtime logs never affect durable state\n- **Deterministic IDs**: Run IDs from timestamps, scenario IDs from comments\n- **Sealed Enums**: `FlowPreset`, `StageId` are fixed, no user extension\n- **Fail-Fast Preflight**: All stage targets validated before first mutation\n\n---\n\n### **Master Prompt Alignment**\n\nAll requirements from the rb.md specification document are met:\n\n✅ Product renamed to `ralph-burning`  \n✅ Workspace root as `.ralph-burning/`  \n✅ 4 built-in flow presets (standard, quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement)  \n✅ Structured JSON stage contracts  \n✅ Markdown as derived output only  \n✅ 7 bounded contexts with explicit contracts  \n✅ Flow immutability per project  \n✅ Durable journal with atomic commits  \n✅ Amendment queue with late-stage semantics  \n✅ Requirements drafting with answer cycles  \n✅ Daemon with task routing and worktree leases  \n✅ Conformance scenario registry  \n✅ Deterministic stage-to-role mapping  \n✅ Failure class taxonomy  \n✅ Session persistence & reuse/reset policies  \n\n---\n\n### **File Statistics**\n\n- **Source files**: 53 Rust files\n- **Test files**: 40+ unit test files + 18 Gherkin feature files\n- **Lines of code**: ~15,000 (source + tests)\n- **Cargo dependencies**: 13 (tokio, clap, serde, chrono, toml, uuid, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### **Compilation Status**\n\n- ✅ `cargo check` passes cleanly\n- ✅ `cargo clippy` with `-D warnings` passes\n- ✅ No build warnings\n- ✅ Ready for testing suite execution\n\nThis represents a complete, well-architected greenfield rewrite with strong test coverage, clear separation of concerns, and production-ready error handling."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a00d414d627485d6b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 78023\ntool_uses: 53\nduration_ms: 124855</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62aed473-a912-4db2-a48b-52d5c598eaf3","uuid":"7f3c181f-1d3c-493e-ad1b-8192e47740b0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the ralph-burning-rewrite project to understand what has been implemented. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read ALL loop spec files to understand what each loop implemented:\n   - loops/005-agent-execution-facade/\n   - loops/006-standard-preset-run-start-orchestration/\n   - loops/007-retry-remediation-resume-and-failure-class/\n   - loops/008-completion-rounds-late-stage-acceptance-and/\n   - loops/009-docs-change-and-ci-improvement-flow-execution/\n   - loops/010-requirements-drafting-and-project-seed-handoff/\n   - loops/011-daemon-routing-tasks-leases-and-worktree/\n   - loops/012-quick-dev-flow-public-execution/\n   - loops/013-run-rollback/\n   - loops/014-conformance-runner-and-ci-gate/\n\n2. Check the src/ directory structure to see what modules exist\n\n3. Check if there are any earlier loops (1-4) or baseline code that was already in place\n\n4. Check the CLI implementation to see which commands are implemented\n\n5. Look at tests/conformance/features/ to see what scenarios exist\n\n6. Check for any TODO markers or unimplemented sections\n\nPlease provide a comprehensive summary of what's been built and what might still be missing compared to the master prompt requirements.","agentId":"a00d414d627485d6b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive understanding of the project. Let me create a detailed summary report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: ralph-burning-rewrite Project\n\nBased on thorough exploration of the codebase, specification documents, feature files, and implementation notes, here's what has been built:\n\n### **Project Overview**\n\nThe `ralph-burning-rewrite` is a Rust-based greenfield rewrite of an AI-driven orchestration system. It's a modular monolith implementing sophisticated workflow automation for software delivery, requirements drafting, and daemon-driven task execution. The rewrite departs from the legacy codebase's design, introducing structured JSON payloads, bounded contexts, and a modern CLI vocabulary.\n\n**Current Status**: Actively under development with 14 completed implementation loops (as of March 13, 2026).\n\n---\n\n### **Implemented Slices (Mapping to rb.md Roadmap)**\n\n#### **Slice 1: Rewrite Charter & CLI Vocabulary** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Product renamed to `ralph-burning` throughout\n- Workspace root standardized as `.ralph-burning/`\n- CLI vocabulary: `init`, `flow`, `config`, `project`, `run`, `requirements`, `daemon`, `conformance`\n- 4 built-in flow presets: `standard`, `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, `ci_improvement`\n- 201 Gherkin scenarios defined across 18 feature files\n- Conformance scenario discovery and validation framework in place\n\n#### **Slice 2: Workflow Kernel Primitives & Stage Contract Framework** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `FlowPreset` enum with 4 variants and metadata\n- `StageId` enum with 16 stages covering all 4 presets\n- `StageContract` with schema → domain validation → render pipeline\n- `BackendRole` deterministic mapping (planner, implementer, QA validator, reviewer, completion judge)\n- `FailureClass` enum: TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n- Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic and consistent\n- Payload validation contracts for all stage types\n\n#### **Slice 3: Workspace Governance & Flow Discovery** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `.ralph-burning/workspace.toml` initialization with version support\n- Effective config resolution (runtime overrides > project config > workspace config > code defaults)\n- Active project selection and persistence\n- `flow list` and `flow show` commands\n- Workspace validation and versioning (currently v1)\n- Template source resolution framework\n\n#### **Slice 4: Canonical Project & Run Store** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `ProjectRecord` aggregate with immutable flow preset\n- `RunRecord` with run ID, status, and stage cursor\n- Durable journal with monotonically-increasing sequence numbers\n- Payload store with validated stage outputs\n- Artifact store with rendered Markdown history\n- Runtime log store (separate from durable history)\n- `run status`, `run history`, `run tail` query commands\n- Session management for backend continuity\n- Amendment queue for late-stage changes\n- Rollback point persistence\n\n#### **Slice 5: Agent Execution with Structured Output Guarantee** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `AgentExecutionService` with pluggable backends\n- `BackendSpec` and `ModelSpec` for 4 backend families (Claude, Codex, OpenRouter, Stub)\n- `InvocationContract` enum supporting both workflow stages and requirements\n- Capability checking (structured output support, session reuse, cancellation)\n- Timeout/cancellation with session cleanup\n- Raw output persistence for debugging\n- Test injection seams for all failure modes\n\n#### **Slice 6: First Vertical Slice - Standard Happy Path** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `run start` command end-to-end orchestration\n- 8-stage standard flow execution: prompt_review → planning → implementation → QA → review → completion_panel → acceptance_QA → final_review\n- Prompt review optionally skippable (7 stages when disabled)\n- Preflight validation of all stage targets before any mutation\n- Atomic stage commits: payload → artifact → journal → snapshot\n- Journal event lifecycle: run_started → stage_entered → stage_completed → run_completed/run_failed\n- Terminal run states with error summaries\n- Post-run queries work correctly (status, history, tail)\n\n#### **Slice 7: Resilience Semantics** ✅ COMPLETE\n- QA remediation loop (request_changes causes re-execution)\n- Review remediation loop (request_changes causes re-planning)\n- Prompt review stage with rejection/approval paths\n- Pre-commit invalidation (failed validation causes re-implementation)\n- `run resume` command for recovering mid-run states\n- Failure-class retry policy (transient vs terminal)\n- Session reuse/reset rules per backend capability\n- Cycle counting and attempt tracking\n\n#### **Slice 8: Completion & Final Review** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Completion rounds distinct from work cycles\n- Completion panel stage with consensus logic\n- Acceptance QA with pass/fail outcomes\n- Final review stage (preset-specific enablement)\n- Amendment queue: typed `QueuedAmendment` with source tracking\n- Late-stage vs remediation-stage separation\n- Amendment persistence before state mutation (durable lifecycle)\n- Amendment injection into planning context\n- Completion guard prevents `run_completed` while amendments pending\n- Amendment drain after successful planning commit\n\n#### **Slice 9: Preset Library Expansion** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `quick_dev` preset: PlanAndImplement → Review → ApplyFixes → FinalReview (4 stages)\n- `docs_change` preset: DocsPlan → DocsUpdate → DocsValidation (3 stages, completion disabled)\n- `ci_improvement` preset: CiPlan → CiUpdate → CiValidation (3 stages, completion disabled)\n- Preset-specific stage contracts and validators\n- Preset-specific final-review policy\n- All 4 presets share the same workflow engine\n- Deterministic role mapping per stage across all presets\n\n#### **Slice 10: Requirements Drafting & Project Seed Handoff** ✅ COMPLETE\n- `requirements draft` with clarifying question generation\n- `requirements quick` skipping questions\n- `requirements show` displaying run state\n- `requirements answer` with TOML parsing and validation\n- Draft → Review → Seed pipeline with validated payloads\n- Question set contract: duplicate ID validation\n- Requirements review contract: outcome + findings validation\n- Project seed generation (project.json + prompt.md)\n- Seed pair rollback on failure\n- Persistent seed files for project creation\n- Resume from answer boundary\n\n#### **Slice 11: Automation Runtime** ✅ COMPLETE\n- Daemon lifecycle: `daemon start --single-iteration`\n- Task model with statuses: pending, active, completed, aborted, failed\n- Task routing: label-based and explicit command-based\n- Worktree leasing with persistent leases\n- Worktree rebase onto default branch\n- `daemon status` with task listing\n- `daemon abort` with task transition and cleanup\n- `daemon retry` returning failed tasks to pending\n- `daemon reconcile` for state recovery\n- Attempt counting for failed task retries\n- Journal events for task lifecycle\n\n#### **Slice 12: Cutover & Documentation** 🟡 IN PROGRESS (Loop 14 active)\n- Legacy orchestrator code paths still present but new runtime active\n- Conformance suite mandatory in test matrix\n- Context packs framework in place\n- CLI cutover to new command routing 100% complete\n- Documentation refresh in progress (loops 11-14)\n\n---\n\n### **Core Module Structure**\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── shared/\n│   ├── domain.rs       — Shared enums (FlowPreset, StageId, BackendFamily, etc.)\n│   ├── error.rs        — Unified error types (AppError enum)\n│   └── mod.rs\n├── contexts/           — 7 bounded contexts\n│   ├── workspace_governance/    — Init, config, flow discovery\n│   ├── project_run_record/      — Project/run CRUD, journal, artifacts\n│   ├── workflow_composition/    — Engine, stage execution, retry policy\n│   ├── agent_execution/         — Backend invocation, capabilities, sessions\n│   ├── requirements_drafting/   — Requirements pipeline, contracts, service\n│   ├── automation_runtime/      — Daemon, routing, leases, tasks\n│   └── conformance_spec/        — Scenario discovery, runner, validation\n├── adapters/\n│   ├── fs.rs           — All filesystem persistence (project, journal, runs, amendments, etc.)\n│   ├── stub_backend.rs — Test-only deterministic backend\n│   └── worktree.rs     — Git worktree operations\n├── cli/                — 8 command modules\n│   ├── init.rs         — Workspace initialization\n│   ├── flow.rs         — Flow list/show\n│   ├── config.rs       — Config get/set/show\n│   ├── project.rs      — Project CRUD\n│   ├── run.rs          — Run start/resume/status/history/tail/rollback\n│   ├── requirements.rs — Requirements draft/quick/show/answer\n│   ├── daemon.rs       — Daemon start/status/abort/retry/reconcile\n│   └── conformance.rs  — Conformance list/run\n├── lib.rs              — Library exports\n└── main.rs             — CLI entry point\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Coverage**\n\n**Total Gherkin Scenarios**: 201 across 18 feature files\n\n| Feature File | Scenarios | Coverage |\n|---|---|---|\n| run_start_standard.feature | 20 | Happy path, error cases, preflight, atomic commits |\n| run_completion_rounds.feature | 16 | Completion semantics, amendments, late stages |\n| run_queries.feature | 28 | Status, history, tail queries, filtering |\n| requirements_drafting.feature | 33 | Draft/quick modes, answers, review, seed rollback |\n| project_records.feature | 23 | Project CRUD, flow immutability, state transitions |\n| run_resume_retry.feature | 9 | Resume from interrupted states, retry logic |\n| run_resume_non_standard.feature | 6 | Quick_dev/docs/CI preset resume |\n| daemon_lifecycle.feature | 5 | Task processing, abort, retry, status |\n| daemon_routing.feature | 7 | Label/command routing, task dispatch |\n| run_rollback.feature | 8 | Rollback points, VCS reset, state recovery |\n| run_start_quick_dev.feature | 10 | Quick_dev preset 4-stage execution |\n| run_start_docs_change.feature | 5 | Docs preset 3-stage execution |\n| run_start_ci_improvement.feature | 5 | CI preset 3-stage execution |\n| workspace_init.feature | 3 | Workspace initialization, versioning |\n| workspace_config.feature | 8 | Config precedence, validation |\n| flow_discovery.feature | 2 | Flow list/show commands |\n| stage_contracts.feature | 9 | Contract validation pipeline |\n| active_project.feature | 4 | Active project selection, persistence |\n\n**Unit Tests**: 40+ test files covering:\n- Domain models\n- Contract validation pipelines\n- Renderers (determinism testing)\n- Workflow engine state machines\n- Adapter contracts\n- Journal serialization\n- Amendment queue operations\n- Retry policies\n- Conformance discovery\n\n**CLI Integration Tests**: 63+ end-to-end tests exercising all command paths\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Decisions**\n\n1. **Structured Payloads as Protocol**: JSON contracts replace markdown as machine protocol; markdown remains rendered output only\n2. **Flow Immutability**: Each project has one immutable flow preset for entire lifetime\n3. **Bounded Context Separation**: 7 clear domain contexts with explicit port/adapter boundaries\n4. **Stateless Engine**: Workflow orchestration via free functions, not class hierarchy\n5. **Durable Guarantees**: Journal-first approach with atomic commits\n6. **Late-Stage Semantics**: Completion panel/acceptance QA/final review use separate completion-round tracking\n7. **Amendment Queuing**: Amendments persisted to disk before state mutation\n8. **Preset-Specific Policy**: Final review, validation profiles configurable per flow\n9. **Deterministic Stage Mapping**: `BackendRole::for_stage()` is consistent across all invocations\n10. **Test Injection Seams**: Environment variables enable testing all failure modes without mocking\n\n---\n\n### **Known Gaps & Outstanding Work**\n\n1. **Legacy Code Paths**: Old orchestrator code still exists in multibackend-orchestration; cleanout deferred to Slice 12\n2. **GitHub Integration**: Daemon routing framework exists but GitHub API adapter not yet wired\n3. **Interactive Requirements**: Requirements answer-via-issue flow not yet implemented\n4. **Validation Profile Selection**: Defaults hardcoded; custom validation targets not yet configurable\n5. **Backend Timeout Tuning**: Hardcoded defaults; configuration not yet exposed\n6. **Worktree Management**: Basic operations implemented; cleanup policies incomplete\n7. **Documentation**: Architecture docs in progress (loop 14 active)\n8. **Performance**: No benchmarks; optimization deferred post-MVP\n\n---\n\n### **CLI Command Surface** (Fully Implemented)\n\n```\nralph-burning\n├── init [--workspace-dir PATH]\n├── flow\n│   ├── list\n│   └── show <preset>\n├── config\n│   ├── get [KEY]\n│   ├── set KEY VALUE\n│   └── show\n├── project\n│   ├── create [--flow PRESET]\n│   ├── list\n│   ├── show [ID]\n│   ├── select [ID]\n│   └── delete ID\n├── run\n│   ├── start\n│   ├── resume\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── history [--json]\n│   ├── tail [--logs]\n│   └── rollback --to ID [--hard]\n├── requirements\n│   ├── draft --idea TEXT\n│   ├── quick --idea TEXT\n│   ├── show <run-id>\n│   └── answer <run-id>\n├── daemon\n│   ├── start [--single-iteration]\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── abort TASK_ID\n│   ├── retry TASK_ID\n│   └── reconcile\n└── conformance\n    ├── list\n    └── run [--features PATTERN]\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Data Model** (Core Entities)\n\n- **ProjectRecord**: Immutable project with flow preset, prompt, ID\n- **RunRecord**: Run instance with cursor, status, session tracking\n- **StageCursor**: Current position (stage, cycle, attempt, completion_round)\n- **PayloadRecord**: Validated stage output in canonical JSON\n- **ArtifactRecord**: Rendered Markdown history artifact\n- **JournalEvent**: Append-only audit log with sequence numbers\n- **AmendmentQueue**: Late-stage change requests with source tracking\n- **DaemonTask**: Unit of automated work with routing/status\n- **WorktreeLease**: Claimed worktree with heartbeat\n- **SessionRecord**: Backend session for reuse/reset tracking\n\n---\n\n### **Error Handling Strategy**\n\n- **Unified `AppError` enum**: ~40 variants covering all failure modes\n- **Failure classes**: TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n- **Precondition checks**: Workspace version, active project, run state transitions validated before mutation\n- **Atomicity**: Stage commits roll back payload on artifact failure\n- **Resumability**: All durable boundaries are resumable after failure\n\n---\n\n### **Testing Strategy**\n\n1. **Conformance Scenarios (Gherkin)**: 201 scenarios defining public behavior\n2. **Unit Tests**: Domain model invariants, contract validation, renderers\n3. **Adapter Tests**: Filesystem persistence, mock backends, worktree operations\n4. **CLI Integration Tests**: End-to-end command execution with fixtures\n5. **Determinism Tests**: Stage contracts produce identical Markdown twice\n6. **Failure Mode Tests**: All error paths exercised via environment variable injection\n\n---\n\n### **Performance Characteristics**\n\n- **Stage execution**: Sequential per run (no parallelization within single stage)\n- **Payload validation**: O(n) schema + O(1-n) domain per stage\n- **Journal operations**: Append-only (O(1) append, O(n) scan on resume)\n- **Conformance discovery**: O(m·s) where m=feature files, s=scenarios per file\n- **No database**: All persistence via filesystem (TOML, JSON, Markdown)\n\n---\n\n### **Notable Design Patterns**\n\n- **Port/Adapter**: Clear trait boundaries for filesystem, backends, worktrees\n- **Strategy Pattern**: `InvocationContract` enum routing to stage/requirements handlers\n- **Atomic Commits**: Payload → artifact → journal → snapshot ordering prevents partial state\n- **Best-Effort Logs**: Runtime logs never affect durable state\n- **Deterministic IDs**: Run IDs from timestamps, scenario IDs from comments\n- **Sealed Enums**: `FlowPreset`, `StageId` are fixed, no user extension\n- **Fail-Fast Preflight**: All stage targets validated before first mutation\n\n---\n\n### **Master Prompt Alignment**\n\nAll requirements from the rb.md specification document are met:\n\n✅ Product renamed to `ralph-burning`  \n✅ Workspace root as `.ralph-burning/`  \n✅ 4 built-in flow presets (standard, quick_dev, docs_change, ci_improvement)  \n✅ Structured JSON stage contracts  \n✅ Markdown as derived output only  \n✅ 7 bounded contexts with explicit contracts  \n✅ Flow immutability per project  \n✅ Durable journal with atomic commits  \n✅ Amendment queue with late-stage semantics  \n✅ Requirements drafting with answer cycles  \n✅ Daemon with task routing and worktree leases  \n✅ Conformance scenario registry  \n✅ 